{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of motion compensation, R is set to the rotation matrix of the EM frame (Ψ EM) to Ψ B of the arm.",
    "Additionally, the estimated displacements of the AP and SI motion models update d y and d expressed Ψ EM, respectively.",
    "During needle insertion, R is the rotation matrix defined from Ψ EE to Ψ B of the robotic arm.",
    "The user moves the haptic device handle to perform the displacement d x in the axial direction of the needle expressed relative to Ψ EE (Fig. 2 (a)).",
    "D. Liver phantomThe liver phantom was developed in [22] and mimics the respiratory-induced motion in the liver."
  ]
}